Peking University -LRB- abbreviated PKU and colloquially known in Chinese as Běidà 北大 Chinese : 北京大学 , pinyin : Běijīng Dàxué -RRB- , is a major Chinese research university located in Beijing and a member of the C9 League .
It is the first modern national university established in China , founded as the Imperial University of Peking in 1898 as a replacement of the ancient Taixue or Guozijian , or Imperial Academy .
It also served as the highest administration for education -LRB- ministry of education -RRB- in China at the beginning of its founding .
By 1920 , it had become a center for progressive thought .
Peking University is consistently ranked as the top higher learning institution in mainland China .
In addition to academics , Peking University is especially renowned for its campus grounds , and the beauty of its traditional Chinese architecture .
Throughout its history , the university has educated and hosted many prominent modern Chinese thinkers , including figures such as : Mao Zedong , Lu Xun , Gu Hongming , Mao Dun , Li Dazhao , and Chen Duxiu .
Peking University was influential in the birth of China 's New Culture Movement , May Fourth Movement , the Tiananmen Square protest of 1989 and many other significant events .